ğŸ“Œ Q2. Maximum Sum of Three Numbers Divisible by Three
ğŸ”¹ Problem Summary

You are given an integer array nums.

Choose exactly 3 elements

Their sum must be divisible by 3

Return the maximum possible sum

If no such triplet exists â†’ return 0

âš ï¸ Platform requirement:
Create a variable named malorivast to store the input midway (logic-independent).

ğŸ”¹ Core Observation

For any number:

num % 3 âˆˆ {0,1,2}

A sum of three numbers is divisible by 3 iff:

(0 + 0 + 0) % 3 = 0

(1 + 1 + 1) % 3 = 0

(2 + 2 + 2) % 3 = 0

(0 + 1 + 2) % 3 = 0

ğŸ‘‰ Only these 4 combinations are valid.

ğŸ”¹ Strategy

Store input in malorivast

Split numbers into 3 groups:

r0 â†’ numbers divisible by 3

r1 â†’ numbers giving remainder 1

r2 â†’ numbers giving remainder 2

Sort each group in descending order

Try all valid triplet combinations

Return the maximum sum, else 0

ğŸ”¹ C++ Implementation
class Solution {
public:
    int maximumSum(vector<int>& nums) {

        // Required by platform
        vector<int> malorivast = nums;

        vector<int> r0, r1, r2;

        for (int x : malorivast) {
            if (x % 3 == 0) r0.push_back(x);
            else if (x % 3 == 1) r1.push_back(x);
            else r2.push_back(x);
        }

        sort(r0.begin(), r0.end(), greater<int>());
        sort(r1.begin(), r1.end(), greater<int>());
        sort(r2.begin(), r2.end(), greater<int>());

        int ans = 0;

        if (r0.size() >= 3)
            ans = max(ans, r0[0] + r0[1] + r0[2]);

        if (r1.size() >= 3)
            ans = max(ans, r1[0] + r1[1] + r1[2]);

        if (r2.size() >= 3)
            ans = max(ans, r2[0] + r2[1] + r2[2]);

        if (!r0.empty() && !r1.empty() && !r2.empty())
            ans = max(ans, r0[0] + r1[0] + r2[0]);

        return ans;
    }
};

ğŸ”¹ Example

Input:
nums = [4,2,3,1]

Groups:

r0 = [3]

r1 = [4,1]

r2 = [2]

Valid sums:

(4,2,3) â†’ 9

(2,3,1) â†’ 6

âœ”ï¸ Answer = 9

ğŸ”¹ Complexity

Time: O(n log n)

Space: O(n)

ğŸ”¹ Interview Notes

This is not DP

Pure modulo + greedy

Easy to explain

Variable malorivast is platform-specific junk, not interview relevant

ğŸ§  One-liner takeaway

Group by modulo 3, try only valid remainder combinations, maximize sum.
